
**Using the Makefile
**This Makefile provides a streamlined way to manage your Dockerized project. Follow the instructions below to perform common tasks.

# Prerequisites
Before using the Makefile, ensure that you have the following installed on your system:

- Docker
- Docker Compose

```console
Available targets:

make pull	   - pull new code
make down    - Stop and remove containers (including volumes)
make build   - Build Docker images for the application and MySQL
make up      - Start the application in detached mode
make clean   - Remove unused Docker images
make deploy  - Build and start the application
make help    - Display this help message
```

# Troubleshooting
If you encounter any issues or errors, refer to the error messages and check the following:

Docker and Docker Compose are installed.
The Dockerfile and Docker Compose files are correctly configured.
Permissions and paths are set up correctly in your project.
Feel free to reach out if you need further assistance!
